  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Discussed in https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/discussions/29887\r\n\r\n<div type='discussions-op-text'>\r\n\r\n<sup>Originally posted by **Doctor-love** December 15, 2022</sup>\r\nHi y'all,\r\n\r\nIs it possible in Quarkus to restrict from which IP addresses the X-Forwarded-*  headers are parsed/trusted?\r\nA similar option exist in nginx called [\"set_real_ip_from\"](https://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_realip_module.html#set_real_ip_from).  \r\n  \r\nMy use-case is exposing a distributed application both via a load balancer and direct connections, but for traceability I don't want to enable trivial spoofing of source IP addresses. Something like \"_quarkus.http.proxy.allow-forwarded-from=ip.address.of.loadbalancer_\" would be useful.</div>",
